      "Ternus, an engineer who has spent more than two decades inside Apple's hardware organization, is closely associated with the silicon transition that produced the M-series chips and with the iPad and Mac product lines. His ascent reflects the board's apparent judgment that Apple's next chapter will be defined more by what it builds than by how efficiently it operates. That is a meaningful shift. Cook's tenure was defined by operational mastery; Ternus will be judged on whether he can rediscover the company's appetite for risk at a moment when generative artificial intelligence is reshaping consumer expectations of every device.",
